node.text:
🙌🏽 In honor of Cinco De Mayo, a major chapter in the origins story of modern day Mexico, my mom explains the meaning behind our families “origins mural” a mural of my grandparents journey from their small village in Mexico, to the fruit fields in Texas, and eventually to beautiful California. They sacrificed and worked themselves to the bone to give their children a better life, the American Dream.

❤️ Knowing where you came Fuels the journey to where you are going 🙏🏽
-
Grateful for the sacrifices of not only my grandparents but also of my parents as well to give me and my brothers a better life🙏🏽
-
#MexicanItalian #Family #grateful

node.text:
This month I’m running for a cause the 𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐡𝐮𝐚 𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐞 𝐇𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐞𝐧 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐫𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩 𝐅𝐮𝐧𝐝 leading up to this years 6th Annual Hackin' for Harden memorial golf tournament , in honor of my childhood friend 𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐡𝐮𝐚 𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐞 𝐇𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐞𝐧 . All our proceeds go to college scholarships in Josh’s name with the 𝐅𝐢𝐫𝐬𝐭 𝐓𝐞𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐏𝐡𝐨𝐞𝐧𝐢𝐱, 𝐬𝐨 𝐭𝐡𝐚𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐲 𝐦𝐚𝐲 𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐧𝐮𝐞 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐢𝐫 𝐩𝐚𝐬𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐨𝐟 𝐠𝐨𝐥𝐟 𝐢𝐧 𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐠𝐞. 

🏌️‍♂️ This event is JUNE 5th in Phoenix AZ and registration is now open! @hackinforharden
-
❤️My childhood friend 𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐡 𝐇𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐞𝐧  was taken from us way too soon 6 years ago in April, Josh contracted an aggressive form of cancer and was gone in 75 days from the time of the diagnosis, He was only 32.
-
❤️𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐡 loved golf and in-fact it was his chosen profession as a certified TPC Caddy. Josh loved the First Tee and what it provides to kids who have never experienced golf before.
-
❤️Each year this event @hackinforHardin is a great opportunity to honor and celebrate Josh, while simultaneously giving back to an organization and sport that was his passion.
-
❤️Since 2015, with generous participation from golfers and supporters like you, the year over year donations to the 𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐡𝐮𝐚 𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐞 𝐇𝐚𝐫𝐝𝐞𝐧 𝐒𝐜𝐡𝐨𝐥𝐚𝐫𝐬𝐡𝐢𝐩 𝐅𝐮𝐧𝐝 have steadily grown, bringing meaningful purpose and a lasting legacy in honor of Josh.
-
🏃🏻‍♀️❤️🏌️‍♂️💰𝐈’𝐦 𝐫𝐮𝐧𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐨 𝐫𝐚𝐢𝐬𝐞 𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐲 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐚𝐥𝐬𝐨 𝐜𝐞𝐥𝐞𝐛𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐉𝐨𝐬𝐡’𝐬 𝐥𝐞𝐠𝐚𝐜𝐲, 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐲𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐬𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐬 𝐡𝐚𝐬 𝐬𝐡𝐚𝐩𝐞𝐝 𝐦𝐲 𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐞 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐛𝐞𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐝𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐦𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐲 𝐭𝐨 𝐣𝐨𝐬𝐡𝐞𝐬 𝐟𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐭𝐨𝐨 𝐜𝐚𝐧 𝐡𝐞𝐥𝐩 𝐩𝐮𝐭 𝐚 𝐤𝐢𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐫𝐨𝐮𝐠𝐡 𝐜𝐨𝐥𝐥𝐞𝐠𝐞 𝐰𝐡𝐢𝐥𝐞 𝐩𝐥𝐚𝐲𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐬𝐩𝐨𝐫𝐭 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐲 𝐥𝐨𝐯𝐞!
-
💰 @jonathan_coyle has pledged $10 for every mile I run leading up to June and you guys can do the same through the 𝗚𝗼 𝗳𝘂𝗻𝗱 𝗺𝗲 𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗸 𝗶𝗻 𝗺𝘆 𝗕𝗶𝗼 👆🏼
-
🙏🏼Always remembered never forgotten love you Josh! #RestEasy

node.text:
You guys already know Sundays are our most important workout of the week🙏🏼🇺🇸 @nemfit 
-
Every Sunday will be a “HERO WORKOUT” dedicated to a fallen first responder or member of the military who has died in the line of duty. Some of the hero metcons are “official” CrossFit Hero WODs (meaning they have appeared on the CrossFit Main Site). Wherever possible I’ll provide backstory and cite the source.
-
🙏🏽“WILL LINDSAY”🇺🇸
-
🔂10 Rounds for Time Of:
-
✅3 Devil Presses
✅22 Alternating Dumbbell Lunges
✅19 Air Squats
-
This Hero WOD honors Sgt. 1st Class Will D. Lindsay, 33, who paid the ultimate sacrifice on March 22, 2019.
-
Sgt. 1st Class Lindsay was a Green Beret of the 2nd Battalion, 10th Special Forces group, on his seventh combat deployment when he was killed by small arms fire during a firefight in Kunduz province, Afghanistan.
-
A recipient of five Bronze Star medals and a Purple Heart, SFC Lindsay was well-recognized for his leadership abilities and combat skills.
-
SFC Lindsay is survived by his wife and four daughters.
-
We first found this workout posted on competitive athlete Josh Bridges’ YouTube channel (@bridgesj3) on May 19, 2019. As Bridges describes it, he was approached by a close friend of SFC Lindsay’s, identified only as “Evan”, during a fitness expo in Utah. During their conversation, Evan told Josh about SFC Lindsay and requested Josh create a workout in his name.
-
The rep scheme signifies the date SFC Lindsay died and 10 rounds signifies the 10th Special Forces Group.
-

💫Greater joint range of motion and freedom of movement
